<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n13114c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n13" href="#n13114c">N13 (VI.D.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n13all.htm#n13114c"> 114(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="green">[chin]</font> Leary</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The legend is that when the saint was first summoned to <mark>King Laoghaire&apos;s</mark> <font color="green">[Leary&apos;s]</font> presence at Tara, after having insulted him by kindling the Paschal fire within sight of the palace, he was dismissed for that time with scant courtesy, but was afterwards sent for by the king to explain his &ldquo;new way&rdquo; to the nobles assembled at Tara <small> Douglas Hyde, <a name="SEGL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SEGL"><cite title="source">The Story of Early Gaelic Literature</cite></a> (1920) 145</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05053c" href="c5all.htm#c05053c">VI.C.05:053(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
